 can just do:<br />&gt;<br />&gt; if (likely(flags &amp; X86_EFLAGS_IF))<br />&gt;   sti();<br />&gt; else<br />&gt;   cli();<br />&gt;<br />&gt; at some cost to code size but hopefully little to no runtime cost for<br />&gt; the sane cases.<br /><br />No, that would be horrible for the case where we had an irq spinlock<br />in an irq-region. Then we'd have a pointless "cli" there.<br /><br />So I'd rather just make sure that only the spinlock code actually uses<br />native_restore_fl().<br /><br />And yes, the patch works at least minimally, since I'm writing this<br />with a kernel compiled with that.<br /><br />Of course, somebody really should do timings on modern CPU's (in cpl0,<br />comparing native_fl() that enables interrupts with a popf)<br /><br />    Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
